  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd 15 \u0b86\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "15 thousand cardiac patients waiting for surgery due to shortage of medicines",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dr. Jayantha Bandara, secretary of the All Sri Lanka Medical Officers Association, said that due to the fuel crisis, lack of medicines and medical equipment, and difficulties in obtaining nutritious food, about 60 lakh people in the country are in dire straits.",
        "He further mentioned that the health of children, the health of pregnant mothers and the health of those suffering from nutritional and infectious diseases have deteriorated massively and there are currently around 15 thousand heart patients on the waiting list for surgery in the country.",
        "\"This is a very dangerous situation. If the government does not take immediate action, the situation will worsen. Due to fuel shortage, the number of patients visiting hospitals has decreased.",
        "About 25-30 lakh people are suffering from infectious diseases in our country every month. People with diabetes and heart disease are unable to get medicines.",
        "About 15 lakh children under 5 years of age are referred to clinics across the country every month.",
        "Currently, Family Health Service Officers and Public Health Inspectors are unable to run clinics. Due to fuel crisis. It seriously affects the health of children.",
        "About 3 lakh people become pregnant mothers every year. Due to this fuel crisis, they are also badly affected. Pregnant mothers are facing serious consequences due to malnutrition.",
        "Amid rising prices of essential food items, it is difficult for them to get the necessary nutritious food. Pregnant mothers and children are the most affected due to the increase in the prices of essential commodities. This can lead to protein and vitamin deficiencies in the future,\" he said."
      ],
